# Prompt History

This document stores major prompts used to generate and revise the C&C Feed Inventory wireframes.

## Current App Context

C&C Feed Inventory is a mobile-first feed inventory and invoicing app.

Core rules:
- C&C owns the feed inventory.
- K2 is a separate cattle-side account.
- Family use is tracked by controlled person records.
- Main inventory-removal flow is called Take Feed.
- Bottom nav: Home, Inventory, Take Feed, Invoices, Accounts.
- Top-right user icon opens profile/settings/login/user role options.
- Cost per unit is role-based and only visible to Admin/Manager.
- Product value = current quantity × sale price.

## 01 — Take Feed Parent Flow

Home → Take Feed → Who is this for?

Branches:
- Customer
- K2
- Family

## 02 — Customer Flow

Customer → Choose Customer → Add Products → Quantity Modal → Review Invoice → Invoice Created

Key requirements:
- Outside customer sale.
- Creates invoice.
- Reduces inventory.
- Can record payment now or later.

## 03 — K2 Flow

K2 → Add Products → Quantity Modal → Review K2 Statement → K2 Statement Created

Key requirements:
- K2 is preselected.
- Skips customer selection.
- Creates K2 statement.
- Reduces C&C inventory.
- Excluded from standard customer sales by default.

## 04 — Family Flow

Family → Who took it? → Family Use Add Products → Quantity Modal → Review Family Use → Family Use Recorded

Key requirements:
- Uses controlled person records.
- Avoid duplicate people like Tessie, Tessie G., and Tessie Geringer.
- Tracks who took what.
- Can be Track Only, Needs Payment, Paid, or Written Off.

## 05 — Add Stock

Home → Add Stock → Select Product → Enter Quantity Added → Review Stock Update → Stock Added

Key requirements:
- Increases inventory.
- Creates restock transaction.
- Does not create invoice.
- Cost per unit visible only to Admin/Manager.

## 06 — Inventory

Home → Inventory → Inventory List → Product Detail

Product Detail actions:
- Take Feed
- Add Stock
- Adjust Count
- View History

## 07 — Invoices

Home / Bottom Nav → Invoices → Invoice Detail → Record Payment → Payment Recorded

Key requirements:
- Shows Customer invoices, K2 statements, and Family records.
- Filters: All, Unpaid, Paid, Customer, K2, Family.
- Recording payment updates status and balance.
- Recording payment does not change inventory.

## Reusable Instruction for Figma

Continue building on the existing C&C Feed Inventory low-fidelity mobile wireframe.

Do not create a new app concept. Do not redesign the style.

Keep the existing:
- grayscale low-fidelity style
- mobile frame size
- spacing
- typography
- card style
- button style
- bottom nav
- top-right user icon
- arrow/flow style
